Subject: [PATCH] provenance: record make+shell variable assignments in the box
 DB
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Complex builds pass values make → shell → sub-make and back; tracing a
wrong value ("aabb") needs the whole assignment chain, searchable in the
box DB — not stderr traces behind magic flags.

New makevar table (name, loc, value, make_dir; UNIQUE-deduped) fed by:
- kati: a VarAssignHook in eval_assign records every makefile-level
  assignment at its ASSIGNMENT site (stmt loc — += points at the append,
  not the original :=), skipping bootstrap/command-line noise.
- brush: an AssignObserver in apply_assignment plus a hook in the export
  builtin record shell scalars and `export NAME=…` inside recipes/
  pipelines, tagged "recipe of <edge>" / "pipeline #<uid>". The box
  export-prefix replay is suppressed (SUPPRESS_VAR_RECORD) so per-
  subshell export noise never lands in the table.

Rows batch through a make_vars frame (256/flush) into the box sqlar;
review.makevars searches name/value with text globs. test_make_rs.py
case 24 pins the full chain: make :=/+= with file:line locs, shell
scalar, export builtin, sub-make override, and prefix suppression.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B97aMMA3rHQW7gsyBB2Cpa
---
 src/export.rs | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/export.rs b/src/export.rs
index af7870c..ba5d5f8 100644
--- a/src/export.rs
+++ b/src/export.rs
@@ -117,6 +117,12 @@ impl ExportCommand {
                     }
                 };
 
+                // sarun: report to the engine's variable-provenance observer
+                // (apply_assignment doesn't see builtin-arg assignments).
+                if !self.unexport {
+                    brush_core::interp::observe_assignment(
+                        name, &value.to_string(), true);
+                }
                 // Update the variable with the provided value and then mark it exported.
                 context.shell.env_mut().update_or_add(
                     name,
